The paper focuses on a storage engine designed specifically for blockchain and forkable applications, which suggests a strong emphasis on data management and storage. This aligns with the scope of the cs.DB (database) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions tamper-evidence and collaboration workflows, which are common security concerns in the cs.CR (cryptology) and cs.SE (software engineering) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also discusses the performance and space requirements of the storage engine, which are key considerations in the cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-categories.
